A monster in a mud is kind of a robot player, there are various types
of "monsters", you can make them passive, agressive, you can make them
react to players actions or other environmental effects.

Descriptions:
You can set the following descriptions in a monster:

A minimal monster object looks like this:
inherit "/std/monster";

void setup() {
   set_name("rat");
   set_gender( "male" );
   add_adj("filthy");
   set_short("A small filthy rat");
   set_long("The rat smells awful.");
   set_race("rodent");
   set_level(1);
   set_hit_skill("combat/unarmed");
   set_skill("combat/unarmed", 50);
   set_skill("combat/defense", 100);
}

